# SDD System

## PLAN Mode Philosophy

Every SDD command follows **plan-approve-execute**: analyze, plan, approve, execute, document. No file changes until the user approves the plan.

**Four phases:** Analysis (readonly) → Planning (create plan) → Execution (after approval) → Documentation (tracking).

See [workflow.mdc](.cursor/rules/workflow.mdc) for orchestration: planner → developer → verifier.

## When to Use Brief vs Full SDD

**Use brief** (feature-brief.md, ~30 min): single team, familiar tech, clear requirements, low risk, &lt;2 weeks, existing patterns, independent feature.

**Use full SDD** (spec → plan → tasks): multiple teams, new/unfamiliar tech, complex stakeholders, high risk or compliance, 3+ weeks, architectural changes, complex integrations.

**Escalation:** If brief takes &gt;30 min or complexity emerges, upgrade to full SDD. Use `/evolve` for living doc updates during development.

## Command → Phase Mapping

| Output        | Template path                    |
| ------------- | -------------------------------- |
| feature-brief | `.sdd/templates/feature-brief-v2.md` |
| plan          | `.sdd/templates/plan-compact.md` |
| tasks         | `.sdd/templates/tasks-compact.md` |

Config: `.sdd/config.json`. Specs live in `specs/active/[task-id]/`.

